# AKIS MCP Gateway Environment Configuration
# 
# This file is used by Docker Compose to configure the MCP Gateway service.
# Copy this file to .env.mcp.local and fill in your actual values.
#
# SECURITY WARNING: Never commit .env.mcp.local to version control!
# The .env.mcp.local file is gitignored for your safety.
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file: cp env.mcp.local.example .env.mcp.local
# 2. Get your GitHub Personal Access Token from: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 3. Required scopes: repo, read:org, read:packages (optional)
# 4. Replace the placeholder below with your actual token
# 5. Start the gateway: ./scripts/mcp-up.sh

# GitHub Personal Access Token (required)
# Generate at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# Required scopes: repo, read:org
GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_token_here

# MCP Gateway Configuration (optional overrides)
# MCP_GATEWAY_PORT=4010
# LOG_LEVEL=info

